ica all three forms of the name are approximately equally common.  See also  Alun ."]},{"name":"Albert","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Albert</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, displacing the Old English form <i>Æþelbeorht</i>. The name is popular in a variety of forms in Western Europe, and has been traditional in a number of European princely families. It was out of favour in England for centuries, however, and the revival of its popularity in the 19th century was largely in honour of  Queen Victoria's  consort,  Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eonion ap Rhys Goch was born about 1120, in Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Rhys Goch ap Llywelyn Fychan, was 22 and his mother, Llywelyn Fychan, was 18. He had at least 1 son with Rhys Goch."},"et":{"about 1120–":"umbes 1120–Surnud","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","1124–Female":"1124–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1100–Male":"1100–Surnud","1104–Female":"1104–Surnud","about 1140":"umbes 1140","1104":"1104","1124":"1124","1100":"1100","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","about 1120":"umbes 1120","of Flint,Wales":"Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1120–":"noin 1120–Kuollut","1120–Male":"1120–Kuollut","1124–Female":"1124–Kuollut","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1100–Male":"1100–Kuollut","1104–Female":"1104–Kuollut","about 1140":"noin 1140","1104":"1104","1124":"1124","1100":"1100","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","about 1120":"noin 1120","of Flint,Wales":"Flintshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales"},"fr":{"about 1120–":"environ 1120–Décédé","1120–Male":"1120–Décédé","1124–Female":"1124–Décédée","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","1100–Male":"1100–Décédé","1104–Female":"1104–Décédée","about 1140":"environ 1140","1104":"1104","1124":"1124","1100":"1100","1120":"1120","1140":"